<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="588" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5082/107.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Special Commissioner <persName type="from">Buchanan</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Willemstadt</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-02-14"><hi rend="italic">February 14,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Protocol signed yesterday at Miraflores in presence of President and
                            Cabinet. Sail early Wednesday on <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> for
                            Guantanamo. The <hi rend="italic">Marietta</hi> will take me from
                            Guantanamo to Washington, where expect to arrive night 26th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Buchanan.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>